Per the conversation _ending_ at https://kubernetes.slack.com/archives/GMDKKM5JP/p1570823892079400 (where I confirm the condition that @deads2k states), I think we should switch to the usual union structure here.  That will make the optionaly comments much less confusing.  Thus:

```
type PriorityLevelConfigurationSpec struct {
    // `nonExempt` holds the configuration if this priority level is _NOT_ exempt, and is empty if this priority level _IS_ exempt.
    nonExempt *NonExemptPriorityLevelConfigurationSpec `json:"nonExempt,omitempty" protobuf:"bytes,1,opt,name=nonExempt"`
}

// NonExemptPriorityLevelConfigurationSpec is the configuration of a non-exempt priority level.
type NonExemptPriorityLevelConfigurationSpec struct {
    ...
}

